* Enable 2FA only after testing it with a phone
 - Input QR code field, check if they match, do not enable it if they don't

* Generate 3 single-use codes to the user, so they can unblock their account if losing their phone
 - send them out in a secure email
 - they can be used anytime (but only once) instead of a dynamically generated code

* Support regenerating QR-code / secret so users can recreate their Google Authenticator accounts
 - test with 2 phones to see whether the old account is automatically invalidated (good) or updated (BAD)

* Style the forms so they look nicer